{
  "id": "tier5_indus_decipherment",
  "name": "Tier 5 — Indus Script Decipherment Hypothesis Test",
  "description": "Tests Dravidian vs Sumerian as target language hypotheses for the Indus Script (Tier 5 logo-syllabic). Applies the Fuls anti-circularity protocol: TokenFilter(min_freq=8) removes hapax signs; only phonogram candidates feed decipherment. Uses SADecipher (GPU-accelerated, 3 parallel seeds) rather than BeamDecipher — SA is far faster for the large Indus sign inventory (~100 phonogram signs). Structural entropy + WritingSystemClassifier run in parallel. All results merged and exported.",
